  <main>
    <h2>Welcome to the Students Attendance System</h2>
    <p>
      The Students Attendance System is designed to simplify and streamline the process of tracking student attendance in academic courses.
      It follows a three-tier client-server architecture, integrating web and mobile applications.
    </p>
    <p>
      <h3>Architecture Breakdown:</h3>
      <h4>Presentation Tier (Client-Side):</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Responsibility: Handling user interface and interaction.</li>
        <li>Components:
          <ul>
            <li>HTML & CSS: Structuring and styling the user interface.</li>
            <li>Client-Side JavaScript: Handling user interactions and making asynchronous requests to the server.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Application Tier (Server-Side):</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Responsibility: Handling business logic, processing user requests, and communicating with the database.</li>
        <li>Components:
          <ul>
            <li>Node.js: The server-side runtime environment.</li>
            <li>Express: A web application framework for Node.js.</li>
            <li>Routes and Controllers: Defining API endpoints and handling logic.</li>
            <li>Business Logic: Logic related to attendance tracking, authentication, etc.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Data Tier (Database):</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Responsibility: Managing and storing application data.</li>
        <li>Components:
          <ul>
            <li>MySQL: The relational database system.</li>
            <li>Database Schema: Defining tables, relationships, and constraints.</li>
            <li>Queries: SQL queries for interacting with the database.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
